@page "/about"
<PageTitle>About — ulfbou.github.io</PageTitle>
<h1>About this place</h1>
<p>This site is a small public logbook for ongoing work. It is meant to answer: what is Ulf working on, what changed recently, and where can someone dig deeper?</p>
<p>It is intentionally not a portfolio. There are no case studies, no résumé blocks, and no attempt to make every project look finished.</p>
<h2>How to read it</h2>
<p>Start with This week. If something sounds interesting, follow it into the map, the notes, or the source.</p>
<h2>Colophon</h2>
<p>The public notes and current state are stored as small Markdown and JSON files. The site is static, hosted on GitHub Pages, and built with .NET 10 Blazor WebAssembly. There is no tracking and no backend.</p>
